I would love to build one of these old arcade boxes, maybe Mr.Do Run Run or even Mr. Do.

Old Skool Massive

nothing better then the real deal, but even if non of these are get built, the cabinet designs and audios systems(which was the reason i compiled all these to begin with) could be easily combined with a modest computer system to run emulation. then...you could use a usb interface from an old usb computer keyboard to set the arcade controls as triggers for the emulator. usb interface+arcade buttons=emulator button programming. i used an old apple keyboard with a sega controller to do it, stupid simple.
